It is easy to install Fotorama:

```xml
<!-- 1. Link to the newest jQuery, -->
<script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.9.1.min.js"></script>

<!-- fotorama.css & fotorama.js. -->
<link  href="http://fotorama.s3.amazonaws.com/<%= process.env.FOTORAMA_VERSION %>/fotorama.css" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="http://fotorama.s3.amazonaws.com/<%= process.env.FOTORAMA_VERSION %>/fotorama.js"></script>

<!-- 2. Add images to <div class="fotorama"></div>. -->
<div class="fotorama">
	<img src="1.jpg">
	<img src="2.jpg">
	<img src="3.jpg">
</div>

<!-- 3. Enjoy! -->
```

